@startuml PY-002 Sequence Diagram — Tabbed Lesson Page

title PY-002: Example & Try it Tab Flows

actor Learner
participant "LessonPage\n/lessons/[slug]" as Page
participant "RightColumn\n(TabBar)" as Tabs
participant "ExampleTabPanel" as ExPanel
participant "TryItTabPanel" as TryPanel
participant "PyodideProvider" as Provider
participant "Pyodide WASM\n(browser)" as Pyodide

== Page load — Example tab shown by default ==

Learner -> Page : navigates to /lessons/[slug]
Page -> Provider : mount — loadPyodide() in background
Page -> Tabs : render TabBar, active = Example
Tabs -> ExPanel : render static SyntaxBlock\n(code from frontmatter)
ExPanel --> Learner : sees Example tab with code + buttons

== Switching to Try it via tab click ==

Learner -> Tabs : clicks "Try it" tab
Tabs -> TryPanel : show TryItTabPanel
TryPanel -> TryPanel : pre-populate editor\nwith starter code (frontmatter)
TryPanel --> Learner : sees editor + output panel + buttons

== Switching to Try it via Try it yourself button ==

Learner -> ExPanel : clicks "Try it yourself"
ExPanel -> Tabs : setActiveTab('tryit')
Tabs -> TryPanel : show TryItTabPanel
TryPanel --> Learner : sees editor

== Run — success ==

Learner -> TryPanel : edits code, clicks Run
TryPanel -> TryPanel : clear output panel
TryPanel -> Provider : runCode(editorValue)
note right of Provider
  Pyodide already loaded.
  No server call made.
end note
Provider -> Pyodide : execute code string
Pyodide --> Provider : stdout
Provider -> TryPanel : display stdout in OutputPanel
TryPanel --> Learner : sees result (target < 3s)

== Run — error ==

Learner -> TryPanel : clicks Run (broken code)
TryPanel -> Provider : runCode(editorValue)
Provider -> Pyodide : execute code string
Pyodide --> Provider : stderr / traceback
Provider -> Provider : convert to plain-English message
Provider -> TryPanel : display friendly error in OutputPanel
TryPanel --> Learner : sees plain-English explanation\n(raw traceback never shown)

== Reset ==

Learner -> TryPanel : clicks Reset
TryPanel -> TryPanel : restore editor to starter code
TryPanel -> TryPanel : clear output panel
TryPanel --> Learner : editor back to original state

@enduml
